 <title>What's New in OpenAM <?eval ${serverDocTargetVersion}?></title>

 <para>OpenAM <?eval ${serverDocTargetVersion}?> is a maintenance release
 that resolves a number of issues, including security issues in OpenAM. It is
 strongly recommended that you update to this release to make your deployment
 more secure, and to take advantage of important functional fixes. ForgeRock
 customers can contact support for help and further information.</para>

 <itemizedlist>
  <para>Before you install OpenAM or update your existing OpenAM installation,
  read these release notes. Then update or install OpenAM.</para>

  <listitem>
   <para>If you have already installed OpenAM, see <link
   xlink:href="release-notes#update-from-earlier-release"
   xlink:role="http://docbook.org/xlink/role/olink"><citetitle>To Update From
   OpenAM 10.0.0</citetitle></link>.</para>
  </listitem>

  <listitem>
   <para>If you are installing OpenAM for the first time, see <link
   xlink:href="release-notes#install-fresh"
   xlink:role="http://docbook.org/xlink/role/olink"><citetitle>To Install
   OpenAM</citetitle></link>.</para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>

  <section xml:id="product-enhancements">
   <title>Product Enhancements</title>

   <para>In addition to fixes, this release includes the following limited
   product enhancements.</para>

  <!-- List generated at 11:54:08 20121213 using http://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/rest/api/2/search?jql=fixVersion+%3D+%2210.0.1%22+AND+project+%3D+OPENAM+AND+resolution+%3D+fixed+AND+type+in+%28Improvement%2C+%22New+Feature%22%29+AND+component+!%3D+documentation&startAt=0&maxResults=500&fields=summary-->
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem><para><link xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/OPENAM-1721" xlink:show="new">OPENAM-1721</link>: New method in AMLoginModule to allow customers to determine other user sessions</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para><link xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/OPENAM-1470" xlink:show="new">OPENAM-1470</link>: Running OpenAM as an SP should not require enabling module based auth</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para><link xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/OPENAM-1454" xlink:show="new">OPENAM-1454</link>: Improve RP support for federation when using DAS</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para><link xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/OPENAM-1348" xlink:show="new">OPENAM-1348</link>: Implement get-sub-cfg ssoadm command</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para><link xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/OPENAM-1266" xlink:show="new">OPENAM-1266</link>: Configure option in OpenAM IDP to Proxy all the requests, regardless if the SP allows or not.</para></listitem>
   <listitem><para><link xlink:href="https://bugster.forgerock.org/jira/browse/OPENAM-1048" xlink:show="new">OPENAM-1048</link>: Add client parameter to REST authenticate command</para></listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  </section>

